@dragon788  there is a special format placeholder for that:

from `mag git-log`: 

           o   %G?: show "G" for a good (valid) signature, "B" for a bad signature, "U" for a good signature with unknown validity, "X" for a good signature that has expired, "Y" for a good signature made by an expired key, "R" for a good signature made by a revoked key, "E" if the signature cannot be checked (e.g. missing key) and "N" for no signature

I'm sorry for making this sound so complicated haha. Pseudo-logic is something like:
```
On event: whole file staged {
  if (diff-view is open) {
    if (status-view has file below) {
      select file below in status-view
      show file below in diff-view
    } else if (status-view has file above) {
      select file above in status-view
      show file above in diff-view
    } else {
      // must be no files left in status view
      close diff-view
    }
  }
}
```
(Where `diff-view` is a split view with the `status-view`)
